@startuml approach3-sql-detailed-activity
title **Approach 3: CosmosClient + FakeCosmosHandler — SQL Query Flow (Detailed)**

skinparam backgroundColor #FEFEFE
skinparam ActivityBorderColor #333
skinparam ActivityBackgroundColor #E8F4FD
skinparam PartitionBorderColor #666

start

|Setup|
:Create **new InMemoryContainer**("orders", "/pk");
:Create **new FakeCosmosHandler**(inMemoryContainer);
:Create **new CosmosClient**(connectionString,
new CosmosClientOptions {
  ConnectionMode = Gateway,
  HttpClientFactory = () =>
    new HttpClient(handler)
});

note right
  Connection string is syntactically valid
  but points nowhere — all requests go
  to FakeCosmosHandler, never to network.
end note

|Test Code|
:Call **client.GetContainer**(databaseId, containerId)
→ Container (real SDK proxy —
no HTTP call, lightweight);|

:Call **container.GetItemQueryIterator<T>**(queryText);

#FFF3E0:=== Query Plan Phase (SDK-initiated) ===|

|CosmosClient (real SDK)|
:SDK builds **HTTP POST** request:
**POST** /dbs/{db}/colls/{coll}/docs
Header: x-ms-cosmos-is-query-plan-request: True
Header: Content-Type: application/query+json
Body: { "query": "SELECT * FROM c
  WHERE c.status = 'active'
  ORDER BY c.timestamp DESC" };

|FakeCosmosHandler|
:**SendAsync**(request);
:Route: detect header
x-ms-cosmos-is-query-plan-request
→ **HandleQueryPlanAsync()**;

|CosmosSqlParser|
:**TryParse**(queryText)
→ CosmosSqlQuery AST;

|FakeCosmosHandler|
:Analyze AST to build
**PartitionedQueryExecutionInfo**:
• Scan OrderBy → ["Descending"]
• Scan SELECT for aggregates
  (COUNT, SUM, AVG, MIN, MAX)
• Detect DISTINCT → Ordered/Unordered/None
• Detect OFFSET/LIMIT
• Generate **rewrittenQuery**
  (wraps fields in orderByItems
  + payload for SDK merge-sort);

:Return **200 OK** with JSON body:
{
  queryRanges: [{min:"",max:"FF"}],
  aggregates: [],
  orderBy: ["Descending"],
  distinctType: "None",
  rewrittenQuery: "SELECT …"
};

|CosmosClient (real SDK)|
:Receive query plan response;
:Build execution pipeline from plan:
• **OrderByPipelineStage** (ORDER BY)
• **AggregatePipelineStage** (if aggregates)
• **DistinctPipelineStage** (if DISTINCT)
• **SkipTakePipelineStage** (if OFFSET/LIMIT);
:Return **FeedIterator<T>** to caller;

#E8F5E9:=== Query Execution Phase (per page) ===|

|Test Code|
while (SDKIter.HasMoreResults?) is (yes)
  :Call **ReadNextAsync()**;

  |CosmosClient (real SDK)|
  :SDK builds **HTTP POST** request:
  **POST** /dbs/{db}/colls/{coll}/docs
  Header: x-ms-documentdb-isquery: True
  Header: x-ms-max-item-count: {pageSize}
  Header: x-ms-continuation: {token}
  Header: x-ms-documentdb-query-partitionkeyrangeid: {rangeId}
  Header: x-ms-documentdb-partitionkey: ["pkValue"]
  Body: { "query": "… (rewritten)",
    "parameters": [{"name":"@p1","value":"active"}] };

  |FakeCosmosHandler|
  :**SendAsync**(request);
  :Route: detect header
  x-ms-documentdb-isquery: True
  → **HandleQueryAsync()**;

  :Extract from HTTP request:
  • sqlQuery (body JSON .query)
  • partitionKey (header)
  • maxItemCount (header)
  • continuationToken → parse offset
  • rangeId (header);

  :**_queryLog.Add**(sqlQuery)
  (available via handler.QueryLog
  for test assertions);

  |QueryResultCache|
  :**TryGet**(cacheKey)
  key = hash of query + params + range;

  if (cache hit?) then (yes)
    :Return cached List<JToken> + offset;
  else (no)

    |CosmosSqlParser|
    :**TryParse**(sqlQuery)
    → CosmosSqlQuery AST;

    |FakeCosmosHandler|
    if (ORDER BY detected in AST?) then (yes)

      #FFFDE7:=== ORDER BY Path ===|

      :Call **HandleOrderByQueryAsync()**;

      |CosmosSqlParser|
      :**SimplifySdkQuery**(parsed)
      → strip orderByItems/payload wrapper
      → recover user's original query:
      "SELECT * FROM c
        WHERE c.status = 'active'
        ORDER BY c.timestamp DESC";

      |FakeCosmosHandler|
      :**BuildQueryDefinition**()
      → new QueryDefinition(simplifiedSql)
        .WithParameter("@p1", "active");

      |InMemoryContainer|
      :Call **GetItemQueryIterator<JObject>**
      (queryDefinition, requestOptions);

      |InMemoryContainer.FilterItemsByQuery|
      :**Parse**(simplifiedSql) → AST;

      :GetAllItemsForPartition()
      → List<string> from store
      (partition-filtered, TTL-applied);

      :AugmentWithComputedProperties();
      :ExpandFromSource();
      :ExpandAllJoins();

      #LightYellow:=== WHERE per item ===
      **EvaluateWhereExpression**
      → **EvaluateSqlExpression** (recursive)
      → all expression types:
      Literal, Identifier, PropertyAccess,
      IndexAccess, Binary, Unary,
      FunctionCall (40+ functions),
      Between, In, Like, Ternary,
      Coalesce, Subquery,
      ArrayLiteral, ObjectLiteral|

      :ApplyGroupBy() + aggregates;
      :ApplyOrderByFields()
      → sort by c.timestamp DESC;
      :TOP / OFFSET+LIMIT;
      :ProjectFields() → SELECT *;
      :StripComputedProperties();
      :DISTINCT;
      :UnwrapValueSelect();

      :Return List<string> (JSON);

      |InMemoryContainer|
      :Deserialize → List<JObject>;
      :Create InMemoryFeedIterator<JObject>;

      |FakeCosmosHandler.DrainIterator|
      :**DrainIterator<JObject>()**
      → loop ReadNextAsync()
        until !HasMoreResults
      → materialize ALL results
      → List<JToken>;

      |FakeCosmosHandler|
      :Reconstruct each document
      for SDK's OrderByPipelineStage:
      {
        "orderByItems": [
          {"item": timestampValue}
        ],
        "payload": { …full document… }
      };

    else (no — standard query)

      #E3F2FD:=== Standard Path ===|

      |CosmosSqlParser|
      :**SimplifySdkQuery**(parsed)
      → simplify SDK internal SQL
      (e.g. remove _rid injections);

      |FakeCosmosHandler|
      :**BuildQueryDefinition**()
      → QueryDefinition with parameters;

      |InMemoryContainer|
      :Call **GetItemQueryIterator<JToken>**
      (queryDefinition, requestOptions);

      |InMemoryContainer.FilterItemsByQuery|
      :Parse(sql) → AST;
      :GetAllItemsForPartition();
      :AugmentWithComputedProperties();
      :ExpandFromSource();
      :ExpandAllJoins();

      #LightYellow:WHERE → EvaluateWhereExpression()
      → EvaluateSqlExpression() (recursive)|

      :ApplyGroupBy() + aggregates;
      :ApplyOrderByFields();
      :TOP / OFFSET+LIMIT;
      :ProjectFields();
      :StripComputedProperties();
      :DISTINCT;
      :UnwrapValueSelect();

      :Return List<string>;

      |InMemoryContainer|
      :Deserialize → List<JToken>;
      :Create InMemoryFeedIterator<JToken>;

      |FakeCosmosHandler.DrainIterator|
      :**DrainIterator<JToken>()**
      → materialize all results;

      |FakeCosmosHandler|
      :Wrap aggregates for SDK if needed:
      • AVG → {"sum": val, "count": 1}
      • COUNT → {"$1": n}
      • SUM/MIN/MAX → {"$1": val}
      (SDK's AggregatePipelineStage
      merges across partitions);

    endif

    |FakeCosmosHandler|
    :**FilterDocumentsByRange**
    (documents, rangeId, payloadPropertyName)
    → hash each doc's partition key
    → keep only docs in this range;

    |QueryResultCache|
    :**Set**(cacheKey, allDocuments)
    TTL from FakeCosmosHandlerOptions.CacheTtl
    (default 5 min);

  endif

  |FakeCosmosHandler|
  :**BuildPagedResponse**()
  → allDocuments.Skip(offset).Take(maxItemCount)
  → Generate continuation token:
    offset-based if more results,
    null if last page
  → Serialize JSON body:
    { "_rid": "collectionRid",
      "Documents": [ …page… ],
      "_count": pageSize };

  :Set response headers:
  • x-ms-request-charge: 1
  • x-ms-activity-id: {new Guid}
  • x-ms-session-token: 0:0#1
  • x-ms-item-count: {count}
  • x-ms-continuation: {token|null};

  :Return **HttpResponseMessage** (200 OK);

  |CosmosClient (real SDK)|
  :Receive HTTP response;
  :SDK pipeline stages process results:
  • OrderByPipelineStage reads orderByItems,
    merge-sorts across partition ranges
  • AggregatePipelineStage accumulates
    {sum,count} → weighted AVG
  • DistinctPipelineStage deduplicates
  • Deserialize JSON → T;

  :Create **FeedResponse<T>**;

  |Test Code|
  :Receive **FeedResponse<T>**
  → .Resource (items)
  → .ContinuationToken
  → .RequestCharge
  → .Count;

endwhile (no)

stop

@enduml
